Package randoop.types

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractTypeVariable
    An abstract class representing type variables including type variables that are type parameters, and those constructed from capture conversion.
    ArrayType
    Represents a Java array type as defined in JLS, Section 4.3.
    CaptureTypeVariable
    Represents a type variable introduced by capture conversion over a wildcard type argument.
    ClassOrInterfaceBound
    Represents a parameter bound which is a class or interface type.
    ClassOrInterfaceType
    An abstract class representing Java class or interface types as defined in the JLS.
    ClassOrInterfaceTypeBound
    Represents a parameter bound that is a class or interface.
    ConcreteTypes
    Constants for concrete Java types.
    GeneralType
    Represents Java types in Randoop, including parameterized types.
    GenericClassType
    Represents the type of a generic class.
    GenericTypeBound
    Represents a type bound in which a type variable occurs.
    GLBTypeBound
    Implements an upper bound on a type variable resulting from a capture conversion (JLS section 5.1.10) in the case that a wildcard has an upper bound other than Object.
    InstantiatedType
    Represents a parameterized type as a generic class instantiated with concrete type arguments.
    IntersectionTypeBound
    Represents an intersection type bound on a type parameter in a class, interface, method or constructor (see JLS section 4.4).
    JDKTypes
    Defines type constants for classes in the JDK Collections.
    ParameterBound
    Represents a type bound on a type variable occurring as a type parameter in a class, interface, method or constructor.
    ParameterizedType
    Represents a parameterized type.
    PrimitiveType
    Represents a Java primitive type.
    PrimitiveTypes
    Implements utilities over Java primitive types.
    RandoopTypeException
    Exception used to indicate when a type problem has occurred in Randoop.
    ReferenceArgument
    Represents a reference type as a type argument to a parameterized type.
    ReferenceBound
    Represents an upper bound on a type variable that is a ReferenceType.
    ReferenceType
    A reference type in JLS (Section 4.3) is defined as one of Class/Interface type, Array type, or a type variable.
    SimpleClassOrInterfaceType
    SimpleClassOrInterfaceType represents a non-generic class, interface, enum, or the rawtype of a generic class.
    Substitution<T>
    Manages the substitution of concrete types for type variables and wildcards in an instantiation of a generic class as a parameterized type.
    TypeArgument
    Represents a type argument of a parameterized type as described in JLS (Section 4.5.1).
    TypeBound
    Represents general upper bound on a type variable of a parameterized type.
    TypeNames
    TypeNames provides a pair of static methods to: get string names for classes and primitive types, and get the Class object for a string representing a class or primitive type.
    TypeTuple
    TypeTuple represents an ordered tuple of type objects.
    TypeVariable
    Represents a type variable that is a type parameter.
    VariableTypeBound
    Represents a type parameter bound that is a type variable.
    WildcardArgument
    Represents a wildcard type argument to a parameterized type.
    WildcardArgumentWithLowerBound
    Represents a wildcard type that has a lower bound (e.g., ? super T).
    WildcardArgumentWithUpperBound
    Represents a wildcard type that has an upper bound (e.g., ? extends T).
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Match
    Enum used to indicate whether types should be matched exactly or using widening.
